1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,158
When you start the activities, they will follow the same order as this lesson.

2
00:00:05,108 --> 00:00:11,385
First, you do a warm-up: Create, type, save, close, find.

3
00:00:11,385 --> 00:00:16,032
Staff will say it once, You repeats or points to prompt cards.

4
00:00:16,032 --> 00:00:20,597
Then you answer quick checks, so we know the key words make sense.

5
00:00:20,597 --> 00:00:30,108
Next, you practise the real computer skill: Open Word, type a note, save it in Documents, close Word, then reopen the file.

6
00:00:30,108 --> 00:00:35,217
You may also type a short answer, for example: Type a short note.

7
00:00:35,217 --> 00:00:42,092
At the end, you finish with a stretch or reflection: Use words, pointing or yes/no choices.

8
00:00:42,092 --> 00:00:45,611
Staff notes barriers and the next support step.

9
00:00:45,611 --> 00:00:48,162
Take one activity at a time.

10
00:00:48,162 --> 00:00:52,703
If you need help, ask staff, then try the next step yourself.

